Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Manager of Corporate Communications and Support Richmond , BC Description Richmond Public Library is looking for a regular full-time exempt Manager of Corporate Communications and Support. This role functions as a key member of the exempt management team and is responsible for leadership, development and oversight of corporate communication strategies as well as providing executive support to the Chief Librarian and the library’s Board of Trustees. This position manages all aspects of corporate communication and executive support, is a key decision maker, is accountable for corporate communication strategies and ensuring that it is in alignment with strategic and operational initiatives. Reporting directly to the Chief Librarian, directly supports the Board of Trustees and collaborates with other library management staff; City staff, including the Mayor and Councillor’s Office; media; vendors; contractors; suppliers; library customers and community groups. Who should apply: The successful candidate is a proven business team member who possesses: A University degree with specialization in Corporate Communications, Public Relations, Journalism or related discipline with minimum 5 years proven leadership and/or management experience in the area of corporate communications, preferably in a unionized library, non-profit or public sector environment.Minimum of 3 years experience supporting senior level executives. Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, written and oral, with proven experience in representing an organization in terms of corporate communications and corporate relations. Richmond Public Library is committed to building a workforce that reflect the diversity of our communities in which we live and serve. We encourage and support applications from Indigenous persons, persons with disabilities, members of the 2SLGBTQIA+ community, and members of visible minority groups. Compensation: Salary range of $93,590 to $116,987 per annum plus comprehensive benefits package. To Apply: Please visit our website at https://www.yourlibrary.ca/about/jobs-at-rpl for more details and to apply. This posting will remain open until filled. Please provide a resume and cover letter describing your career path and outline how you meet the requirements of the position. Personal information submitted will be managed in accordance with the Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act and will be used only to determine eligibility for employment. Applicants must be legally eligible to work in Canada. Preferred candidates will be required to submit a Criminal Record Check. We thank all who apply but only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $93,590 to $116,987 per annum Closes: 19 December, 2023 Richmond Public Library Richmond , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
