Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Services Specialist Toronto , ON Description Posting #: 23-465EXTREP1 Posting Date: September 21, 2023 Closing Date: September 29, 2023 Job Title: Services Specialist Location: Bloor-Gladstone Branch Status: Permanent Full Time HOURS PER WEEK &amp; SCHEDULE OF WORK: (SUBJECT TO CHANGE IN ACCORDANCE WITH ARTICLE 19) 35 hours per week. Evenings and Saturdays required. Weeks 1 &amp; 2: Mon. 12:45pm - 8:45pm Tues. 12:30pm - 8:30pm Wed. 8:30am - 4:30pm Thurs. 9:00am - 5:00pm Sat. 9:00am - 5:00pm (Week 2 only) Plus seven [7] variable hours. JOB SUMMARY: To provide direct and indirect customer service and special service planning and expertise. To coordinate the delivery of a targeted service (e.g., Children’s, Literacy, Multicultural). DUTIES: Under the general direction of the designated supervisor, the position is responsible for: Leadership Functions: providing expert information in the planning process related to specific area of expertise developing service plans related to specific area of expertise developing standards and performance measures developing evaluation methodologies and evaluating performance and outputs leading or participating in project teams and committees developing and implementing training programs related to area of expertise establishing and maintaining contacts in the community related to area of expertise maintaining and disseminating awareness of new research and developments maintaining liaison with supporting branch and department staff Service Functions: providing information services participating in the development of information tools at the system level planning, conducting and evaluating individual programs and events participating in system collection development related to the specific area of expertise performing various duties at the branch and area level such as collection development and community outreach. Qualifications: Graduate degree in Library or Information Science from an accredited institution or equivalent education Minimum of three professional (3) years public library experience, including a minimum of two (2) years in the area of expertiseUnderstanding and appreciation of the philosophy of public service to all, in accordance with human rights legislation and the principles of equity and access in the delivery of library serviceProfessional skills, including in-depth knowledge of special service areaProven ability to lead and to supervise staff Excellent interpersonal, communication and planning skillsDemonstrated sound judgement, problem-solving, and consultative skills Salary: $84,448.00 per annum (2023 Rate)APPLY NOW Compensation $84,448.00 per annum Closes: 29 September, 2023 Toronto Public Library Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
