Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Circulation Team Leader-Full-time union NEWMARKET , ON Description Overview of position The Newmarket Public Library is looking for a pro-active and customer-focused Circulation Team Leader to work full-time in Circulation Services. Reporting to the Manager, Library Services, the Circulation Team Leader you will lead the day-to-day operation of the Circulation Services of the Newmarket Public Library. Key Duties and Responsibilities Create and coordinate the monthly work schedule for staff to meet library operating requirements.Assign weekly tasks and desk schedules.Monitor all library circulation staff to ensure appropriate coverage of public service points and makes arrangements for absences.Implement training processes and monitor regular staff training and retraining to ensure Circulation staff are equipped with the knowledge required to deliver superior customer service.Working with the Manager, Library Services, direct and support maintaining the library’s collection and keeping the library as a welcoming space for the community.Ensure the provision of prompt courteous service and a positive image of the library to the public. Monitor and intervene as necessary in unusual problems, conflicts and disputes with patrons and the public. Prepare monthly reports and statistics on circulation and technology.Assist in the Circulation department with checkout, check in, renewal, collection of fees, answering queries on patrons’ accounts, membership renewal, new membership and orientation, sorting materials for shelving, interlibrary loan, and other library related duties as they evolve through service and technology changes. Responsible for cash handling as required as well as the collections agency.Implement and monitor policies and procedures in order to ensure timely and accurate Circulation services.Provide backup information services to the public as required, such as directing incoming phone calls, answering public queries, conducting reference interviews, providing reader’s advisory service, and assisting in the use of the library’s computer and online resources. Credentials Required Library Technician Diploma with 3-5 years’ experience in a public library environment or a related combination of education and experience. Self-motivated and able to work independently and as part of a team. Familiarity with standard office software and with Integrated Library System software.Familiarity with scheduling software such as SNAP 365 an assetSolid communicator with a focus on internal and external customer service.Ability to lift and carry library materials and equipment up to 50 lbs. approximately and to push and pull full book trucks.Excellent alpha numeric skills, with a good understanding of cataloguing standards. Cash HandlingAbility to deal courteously and effectively with public, staff and stakeholders. Hours of work Hours of work may include Saturday/ Sunday, and evening shifts. Hours of work are in accordance with Section 15.01 of the Full Time Collective Agreement.How to apply Submit a cover letter and resume to jobs@newmarketpl.ca. We thank all applicants for their interest. However, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Newmarket Public Library is committed to accommodating all applicants in accordance with the Ontario Human Rights Code for all employment activities including the recruitment process. The Newmarket Public Library is committed to a barrier-free recruitment and selection process. We uphold our values of diversity, equity, inclusion and anti-racism in the delivery of our services and in our workplace. The Library encourages applications from all applicants, including members of groups with historical employment barriers to equity, this is including but not limited to, Indigenous, Black and Racialized Groups, People with Disabilities, Women and Persons within the 2SLGBTQ+ community. Compensation $55,847-$63,463/annum Closes: 4 October, 2023 Newmarket Public Libary NEWMARKET , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
