Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Deputy CEO Mulgrave , NS Description Eastern Counties Regional Library Job Posting Deputy CEO- Mulgrave, NS Eastern Counties Regional Library (ECRL) is one of nine regional public library systems in Nova Scotia. Since 1969, ECRL has provided public library service to the geographic areas of Inverness, Richmond and Guysborough Counties, amounting to the largest geography of any library system in Nova Scotia. ECRL serves a population of approximately 33,000 people with nine library branches including Atlantic Canada's first Open Library, a self-serve library kiosk, and a Regional Office located in Mulgrave, NS. Under the direction of the CEO, the Deputy CEO provides leadership and strategic planning for all aspects of operations. Areas of primary responsibility include supervision and staff training for the integrated library system (ILS), computer hardware, software, and networks at ECRL. Duties to include (but not limited to): Staff instruction, primarily in the use of the ILS and other technologiesDevelops training materials and communications for all staff in their areas of expertiseInvestigates and troubleshoot problems with the ILS, liaising with Nova Scotia Provincial Library (NSPL) Technical Services staff as requiredSupervises Technical Services staffSupervises branch staff in the use of the ILS, use of technology, and collection of statistics Manages branch staff and operations as neededManages technical services, including cataloguing, acquisitions, processing, internal/external shipping of materials, and collection maintenanceOversees the collection and reporting of all statistics, directing all staff as requiredRuns statistical and data reports for use at ECRL as requiredManages the operation of the Open Library, self-serve kiosk, and self-checkout machinesTroubleshoots, tracks, and resolves technology issues at all ECRL locationsSelects, images, maintains, and manages all public and staff technologyServes as the network administrator for the Regional Office networkTroubleshoots and reports issues with the Edge Routers, wireless access points, and the Ednet WAN to NSPLInventories and documents all hardware, software, and connectivity informationEnsures appropriate security procedures are implemented (i.e., passwords changed) and followed to maintain the integrity of networks, Google Workspace, ECRL website, and the ILSAdministrates ECRL’s Google Workspace account and manages all staff and functional user accounts Administrates ECRL’s website and liaises with website contractor as neededAssesses and selects accessibility technology to both accommodate and support staff needs and to support public use of servicesManages technology-related grants and projects as required and assists with the management of other regional projects as neededParticipates in the development of ECRL’s annual operating budget (i.e., estimating technology and technical services related costs)Participates in the management and resolution of operational issues and challenges, particularly as they relate to their areas of expertiseRepresents ECRL on provincial committees as requiredAttends and takes meeting minutes at ECRL’s monthly board meetings Other duties as required Requirements Master of Library and Information Science degree, or equivalent, from an ALA-accredited institutionDiploma or degree in information technology or extensive experience working with computer technologyIn-depth knowledge of current hardware, software, and networking technologies A proven orientation towards innovation and service to the community Possess strong problem-solving, analytical, and troubleshooting skillsAbility to work in a complex and changing environment, both inside and outside of traditional library activities and settingsAbility to develop and lead projects with minimal supervisionAbility to contribute positively and work effectively within a team environmentKnowledge of integrated library systems (especially Symphony)Knowledge of current cataloguing rules and proceduresStaff supervision and performance management Valid Nova Scotia driver's license and a clean driving abstract for five years What we offer Extended Health &amp; Dental InsuranceGroup RRSPEmployee Assistance ProgramThirteen paid holidays annuallyProfessional development opportunitiesGenerous paid time off to support work life balanceMoving allowance available Posted: September 20, 2023 Application Deadline: October 20, 2023 Job Classification: Management Salary: $65,000-$70,000 Reports to: CEO Eastern Counties Regional Library is an equal opportunity employer. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, you may contact us at jobs@ecrl.ca. Only those applicants who are shortlisted for an interview will be contacted. Eastern Counties Regional Library reserves the right to withdraw the competition if a suitable candidate cannot be found. Please submit by email a cover letter stating your qualifications and interest in the position with a resume and three work references to: Laura Emery, CEO Eastern Counties Regional Library Email:jobs@ecrl.ca Please visit ecrl.ca for more information about us! Compensation $65,000-$70,000 Closes: 20 October, 2023 Eastern Counties Regional Library Mulgrave , NS Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
