Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Director, Education and Impact Toronto , ON Description THE JOB: Develop opportunities to help those working in the Canadian library sector to improve their skills.IN OTHER WORDS: As our Director, Education and Impact, you'll be at the forefront of driving positive change in the library profession. Your mission? Innovate, develop, and evaluate the impact of OLA's programs and services. This role also involves building strong partnerships and understanding the learning and development needs of those working in libraries of all types. You'll oversee the development and delivery of Canada's largest library conference, the OLA Super Conference, and a suite of educational programs.You are interested in what people who work in libraries want to learn, and how they want to learn it. You love to scour the library landscape for interesting thinkers and innovative topics. You know how to make presentations more engaging, workshops more fun and how to get the most out of every meeting. You're able to facilitate remote groups of people in energizing and productive ways. DOES THIS SOUND LIKE YOU?You have a background in libraries, and understand the people who work in them. You are knowledgeable about the development and delivery of adult education.You are able to oversee budgets, track sales goals, and monitoring expenses. You love planning events of all kinds, both in person and virtually.People have told you that you’re a good host and a good collaborator.You are comfortable and experienced with managing teams, and have the ability to make both staff and volunteers feel empowered and appreciated.You are very comfortable with technology. You will be working daily with cloud-based design software, databases and updating content on a variety of platforms. You stay on top of technology trends and explore new technologies that make shared project planning, and event production more efficient and user friendly. HOW WILL YOU SPEND YOUR DAY?You will:Manage the small team coordinating the logistics for our annual calendar of workshops and conferences (approx. 12 per year) Facilitate OLA committees in their work to develop events, training tools, white papers and outreach activities. Create, monitor, update event marketing plans.Monitor and analyze member feedback and create event wrap-up reports for stakeholders. Reach-out to new partners and stay connected to a network of library professionals.Look for opportunities to leverage the work being done throughout the association (strategic plan, fund development, member engagement) through events and training opportunities. STILL READING? GOOD. WE’RE ALSO LOOKING FOR:A service oriented professional with fantastic written skills and strong verbal and presentation skills. A team player who enjoys working with a small, but very dedicated group.A self-starter who can work independently and brings fresh project ideas back to the team.WHY WOULD I WANT TO WORK AT OLA?Remote working environment, with an optional shared office space in downtown Toronto. Be part of a fun, fast-paced, collaborative team. Flexible work options Amazing health and benefits plan and RRSP matching program Please send your cover letter and resume to hr@accessola.com no later than Friday September 29, 2023. Compensation $65,000 - $72,000 Closes: 29 September, 2023 Ontario Library Association Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
