Date: September 14, 2023 Scope and Purpose:
Wheatland Regional Library requires a Temporary Program Manager. Under the direction of the Library Director, this individual will oversee programming for all 45 Wheatland Regional Library branches. The Program Manager is a member of the Wheatland Regional Library management team. Travel within the region is required. Evening and weekend work is required. This is a full-time, six-month term position, with the possibility of extension. Work hours are flexible as determined by travel. Duties and Responsibilities: • Lead the development and execution of strategies and plans for region-wide programming • Coordinate library programs and events including Saskatchewan Library Week, Children’s Book Week, Summer Reading Club, Saskatchewan Indigenous Storytelling Month, and author tours • Coordinate multi-branch programming and community services events and activities • Interact/build relationships with community-based organizations such as literacy groups, community groups, and other service groups • Commitment to deliver consistent programming services to a diverse population • STEAM/STEM programming for children and teens • Develop and recommend to the Library Director an annual budget for programming services • Provide leadership to, communicate with, and support the branches in all aspects of programming • Provide back up to the Branch Manager when required Qualifications: • Master’s degree in Library Science from an ALA accredited institution, completion of a Library and Information Technology diploma from an accredited institution or a post-secondary education with equivalent experience • Previous programming experience including planning, developing and delivering programs • Demonstrated ability to work constructively in a collaborative decision-making process • Strong leadership and management skills • Excellent oral and written communication skills • Ability to program for patrons of all ages • A current acceptable Criminal Record Check is required • Valid driver’s license and the ability to drive throughout the region as required
