Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Manager, Mobile Library Services &amp; Logistics Support Toronto , ON Description Posting #:23-392EXTREP1 Posting Date: September 07, 2023 Closing Date: October 06, 2023 Job Title: Manager, Mobile Library Services &amp; Logistics Support Location:1076 Ellesmere Road and 5120 Yonge Street Collections &amp; Membership Services Status: Permanent Full-Time - EXEMPT About TPL: Toronto Public Library is the busiest urban public library system in the world. Every year, we have millions of users visiting our branches and our online services. We empower Torontonians to thrive in the digital age and global knowledge economy. With expanded access to collections and services, lifelong learning and diverse cultural and leisure experiences, Torontonians have increased opportunities for growth and success, as well as stronger connections to each other and their communities. At TPL, you will be part of an organization with an active learning culture and a deep commitment to making a difference in the lives of Torontonians. Help us grow, innovate, and make a difference.JOB SUMMARY: Reporting to the Director, Collections and Membership Services (CMS) the Manager is responsible for planning, managing and evaluating operations and services of the unit that leads Home Library and Bookmobile Services as well as Fleet and Distribution Services.The Manager supports a team of 65 staff working Monday to Saturday with 23 direct reports in the Mobile unit and the Distribution Services Manager. The Manager is a member of a group of five Collections and Membership Managers. Staff are located at two different physical sites, as well as participating in logistical activities throughout the City. The Manager’s annual key performance indicator is based on the efficient and effective rapid delivery of materials between over 100 locations to ensure both a high level of proactive and responsive customer service. DUTIES: Mobile Library Services and Fleet Plans and manages work related to mobile library services including customer engagement, experience, outreach and promotion.Manages and monitors division for efficient, steady movement of materials to customers with respect to priority and demand.Develops goals and objectives for the area of responsibility and monitors operation in relation to these goals.Manages and validates the writing and updating for all processes in the unit for consistency and ease of use for new team members of local practices.Accountable for the effective management of financial and human resources for both mobile library services and library logistics including fleet and distribution services logistics. Works closely with all CMS managers to ensure the workflows accurately reflect system service objectives.Regularly works with CMS staff and management team to set goals, review projects and regularly assess recommendations for changes in procedures to enhance efficiency.Determines service standards for customers in consultation with system staff.Leads the support of the above with Manager of Distribution Services for system fleet and technical services logistics. People Leadership Hires new staff, transfers, promotes, approves wage increases and conducts performance evaluations.Disciplines, terminates, participates in grievance procedures and administers collective agreements as required.Ensures training and development of staff to optimize quality of work and service deliveryEnsures appropriate staffing levels are maintained (approving/rejecting vacation requests)Communicates frequently with staff on a wide variety of topics, develops staff, coaches for quality service, and manages performance. Planning, Policies and Procedures Effectively communicates policies, programs and priorities of the team and system and aligns and motivates staff to a shared vision.Represents the unit on various system working groups and committees.Monitors external social, economics, political and environmental trends that affect mobile library services and library logistic services. Technology Keeps staff and system up to date on changes related to mobile library and logistical systems including enhancements, updates and outages in relation to both the central sorter and fleet.Develops and maintains a solid understanding of all technology related to the work of the unit through experience, training and other professional development. Regularly analyze and audit useful aspects of the library system and other products and communicate with vendors as necessary. Qualifications: Post-graduate university degree in library or information science from an accredited program, or a recognized library degree equivalent Minimum of three years of experience in a public library environment with a minimum of one year of management experience in a multi-branch system including responsibilities for service evaluation and logistics.Experience managing both public and logistical support services in a large urban public library environment.Experience with various workflows for library materials management with a focus on customer service.In-depth knowledge and experience with an integrated library system and related technology and how the work of the unit affects access to library materials across the system.Thorough knowledge of legislated health and safety requirements related to fleet operations. Ability to demonstrate vision, strategic thinking, collaboration and inclusive leadership skills, flexibility and adaptability and a willingness to embrace and drive change.Ability to recognize and set priorities and to use initiative and independent management decision making.Knowledge of and proven experience applying effective management practices and principles, strategic planning and project management.Strong knowledge and experience using MS Suite of resources and an ILS to effectively lead and manage a large team of staff and extensive workflows.Ability to meet deadlines, set priorities, collaborate, yet work independently.Excellent conflict management and problem solving skills, demonstrated business negotiation skills.A strong commitment to the vision, mission and values of Toronto Public Library and the ability to work effectively with diverse communities and in a diverse work culture.Strong interpersonal skills, with proven ability to coach and lead teams and resolve conflicts.Strong change management skills with ability to influence and build productive relationships with cross-divisional stakeholders. Excellent written and verbal communication and presentation skills; ability to effectively communicate with senior leaders.Proven ability to think conceptually, understand the big picture and convey clearly to others. Note: Must be willing to work various shifts depending upon the needs of the library, including evenings and weekends, onsite between two locations. Salary: $124,140.00 - $160,878.00 per annum (Grade 8, 2023 Rates) APPLY NOW Toronto Public Library does not ask for a credit card, banking information, or social insurance number during the recruitment process. Do not respond to emails or requests for information about jobs at TPL that are not sent from an @tpl.ca address. Toronto Public Library invites applications from all qualified individuals. The Library is committed to employment equity and diversity in the workplace and welcomes applications from visible minorities, Indigenous people, persons with disabilities, and persons of any sexual orientation or gender identity. Upon request, accommodation will be provided for persons with disabilities through all stages of the recruitment and selection process. If you require an accommodation to apply to a Toronto Public Library job posting, please send us an email with your accommodation needs at accommodations@tpl.ca quoting the posting number and the title. If you are invited to participate in the assessment process and require accommodations for the assessment, we ask that you provide your accommodation request as soon as reasonably possible. All accommodation requests are confidential. Toronto Public Library invites applications from all qualified individuals. The Library is committed to employment equity and diversity in the workplace and welcomes applications from racialized people/people of colour, women, Indigenous people, people with disabilities, and 2SLGBTQ+ people. Compensation $123,830.00 - $160,477.00 per annum Closes: 6 October, 2023 Toronto Public Library Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
